{
  "doc_id": "30119",
  "text": "Our results show more differences in plasma derived C activation capacity between patients with UC and CD, which is in concordance with the overall immune activation as indicated by CRP, orosomucoid and leucocyte count, and by the fact that CRP may activate C by initiating the classical pathway [CITATION_1] . The up-regulation in C activation capacity is more pronounced in plasma from CD-patients compared to UC, in accordance with in vitro studies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
